scene.message:
Student: Club Pres, we still{nl}
haven't picked what we're{nl}
doing for the festival.{waitkey}{ret}

Student: I heard the school{nl}
used to have a traditional{nl}
play. Are you doing that?{waitkey}{nl}
Something about snow...{waitkey}{ret}

Club Pres: No! That's{nl}
forbidden!{wait_fr:80} ...I'll decide{nl}
on the program soon.{nl}
Just wait a little longer.{waitkey}{ret}

Nanjo: "Something about{nl}
snow"... You mean{nl}
"The Snow Queen"?{waitkey}{ret}

Mark: Forget the play —{nl}
let me get up there{nl}
and dance!{waitkey}{ret}

Yukino: I had no idea this{nl}
school had a traditional{nl}
play. News to me.{waitkey}{ret}

Student: One trophy from{nl}
nine years ago is missing.{nl}
They won the competition{nl}
that year, but the trophy...{waitkey}{nl}
it's just not there.{nl}
Seriously bugs me.{nl}
Like, for real.{waitkey}{ret}

Student: Wasn't the Club Pres{nl}
acting a little strange?{nl}
Why did she get so{nl}
upset like that?{waitkey}{ret}

Club Pres: What, are you{nl}
here to join? If not,{nl}
you're in the way.{nl}
Please leave.{waitkey}{ret}
